  The use of spPicStat:
    - initialized to NULL at channel setup
    - points to the latest picture that bufferer task sent to splicer task
    - in splicer task, spPicStat always point to the latest picture from
      bufferer task
    - NOTE: should only be set by bufferer task, not in splicer!

  - NOTE: need to check all usage of spPicStat and nextPicStat!

  getNextPicStat(pPicStat) will get the next pPicStat's next PicStat in the
      channel, and in case pPicStat is already the last pic passed to splicer,
      returns NULL!!

  Added code to drop picture when picture type is wrong.  But code has bad
  pidBuf problem and reset.

  Found that the problem is due to the fact that the dropped picture may not
  be the next picture to be sent to mux.  For example, PBB, may be only the
  middle B picture is to be drop, not the P.
  Need to enhance dropPic() to handle picture not being nextPicStat.

  New dropPic() seems to work pretty well. => dpi1186.fls


